AB  - This study investigates the effects of foreign exchange restrictions on the black market premium for dollars in Chile over the period 1975–1984. The model emphasises the interaction of stock and flow conditions in the black market for dollars. Our results support the view that the real exchange rate, the official depreciation-adjusted interest rate differential, the dollar value of peso assets valued at the official exchange rate, and foreign exchange restrictions are important determinants of the black market premium.
